<p class="introduction">
    Previously, we have solved problems based on knowing the heat energy added to a substance \( Q \).
    We have either solved to find this variable, or, knowing this variable, determined other information.
    However, most situations in which the temperature or state of a substance changes,
    involve mixing objects of different temperature.
    In these situations, you cannot measure \( Q \) directly. Instead, you analyze the situation
    from studying final and initial temperatures.
    That is the type of problem we are approaching now.
</p>

